{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, in §B.2 we clarify why worse performance on the test set in our study is attributed to higher rate of hallucinations, as defined in §B.1.",
    "The test set can be conceptually divided into two types of questions.",
    "First, there are questions with answers that are unknown to M.",
    "Those questions will remain unknown post fine-tuning, as we make sure that the training set is disjoint from the test set (§A).",
    "This means that both M D1 and M D2 will fail to answer these questions."
  ]
}